[Made in collaboration with Sedivalle!](https://cults3d.com/en/users/Sedivalle/3d-models)
Thumbnail painted by the excellent Draconian Minipainting!

This pack contains Regular, Heavy Weapons, and Command versions of Sedivalle's Exterminators, resculpted and adjusted for printing at 8mm scale for all of your mass wargames, or scaled up as you see fit!

Options include:
***Small Arms:***
Fist, Claw and Dual Claws. 5x Poses each.

***Command:***
Champion
Banner Bearer with Fist or Bolter
Captain with choice of large or small crest

***Heavy Weapons:***
Heavy Bolters, Plasma, Heat Rays, or Disintegrator cannons.
5x Poses each. Mirroring suggested for additional variety.

Heavy Infantry for teleporting into your foes, Boarding their ships, and killing them dead!

I came up with some variants to represent wartime production of the Indom Pattern, as it was used to mass-produce terminus armour when materials or technology to produce the other patterns became scarce.

Options are the same as my other Terminus packs, including Ranged Weapons, Shields, Heavy Weapons and Dual Claws. Check out the options in the animations in the images!

Note that I've omitted the ordnance variations in order to save space (this is quite a big pack!). If you want grenade launchers or missile launchers, grab the bits from my other models and kitbash them on!

Check out the "_standoffs" version. The models' feet are offset from the plug, allowing you to use the plug as a stand when painting, and then slice or snip off the small cylinders to allow you to glue the feet directly onto the base, for a seamless finish.

Thanks to Moonjammy, Jimmyzimms and KMFP who made the original Terminuses
A BIG thanks to LSTAR, who helped me with the export script for these guys. I wouldn't be able to put out the variety I have without it!

While uploading, i noticed some of the studs are way higher detail than they need to be! Apologies! Hopefully you should be able to exclusively download the files you need, but I hope they shouldn't be too bad!

Inspired by EpicRich's work but a rebuild from the ground up for your Chaotic Elite needs. Figures come with helmets and unhelmeted forms.

FYI: As the original inspiration contained the customary 'chaos means spike rack' I've included an option for them but they may be a nightmare so versions of figures without are present as well (also they were designed for my 15mm Space Hulk needs anyways). The shoulder pads are a sin against all that is holy and LoggyK but done for expediency. Keep a watch here because I will build some custom pads in the future for GC chaos dudes.

Due to the numbers of remixes and various tooling used over the years, we'd seen many mesh errors and misalignments / bad rotations of parts creep into the base design. The Indomitus kit has been extensively worked over to be symmetrical and properly aligned now with all parts being cleaned and normalized.

Blender file source included as well for you to further customize your forces of disorder with.

edit 20221109: Updated the Lord with better posing and added a heavy weapon terminator

Edit 20221118: Added a blender builder file with a reworked and corrected version (or base) of the Tartaros Terminator kit so you can create your chaotic chonky dudes, but with style.

Edit 20221123: Created posed Tartaros Terminators and Blastmaster heavy weapon

If you like what I did and want to leave a tip it would be appreciated.
https://paypal.me/jimmyzimms

Some tiny dudes with grenade launchers from the legion with poor personal hygiene, ready for you to commit tiny war crimes. A basic edit of MoonJam's excellent Heavy Siege Armour guys. Only three poses, but you could sub in the sarge or heavy weapons guys from the original thing if that bothers you.

Intended for resin printers. Contrary to advice on the original models I use 0.05 layer height and 8xAA and can't tell the difference from tabletop distance (I've tried both settings, original was 0.02 & 2xAA).

Should print right out of the box without any additional supports, but spending five minutes running them through Photon File Validator is recommended. I'm just getting started 3d modelling for printing, so if you have issues please let me know.
